'''Haven Base''', also known as '''Arbra Base''',<ref name="EGWT">''[[The Essential Guide to Weapons and Technology]]''</ref> and more informally known as the '''Hole in the Ground''', was the name given by the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebels]] to the base they established in a cavern on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Arbra/Legends|Arbra]]. The base was powered by the cave's [[power rod]]s. It was the main base that replaced [[Echo Base/Legends|Echo Base]], after a brief layover at [[Golrath Station]].

==History==
The cave that eventually housed Haven Base was discovered during a [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] reconnaissance mission led by [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]]. For the Alliance, the remote [[Planet/Legends|planet]], named [[Arbra/Legends|Arbra]], seemed a good choice for the location of a new base of operations after the evacuation of Echo Base on [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]] and [[Golrath Station|the short-lived outpost]] on [[Golrath/Legends|Golrath]].

The Rebels soon found the planet's native [[Hoojib/Legends|hoojibs]] draining the energy from their equipment. The hoojibs' "[[spokesmind]]," [[Plif/Legends|Plif]] communicated with Leia telepathically to explain they had been driven from the cave that supplied them with the energy they needed for sustenance by a creature called the [[slivilith]]. After the Rebels helped the hoojibs defeat the slivilith, they discovered the immense crystalline formations known as power rods inside the cave. The crystals captured the planet's geothermal energy and technicians realized they could tap into that energy to power a new base. Their new allies, the hoojibs, agreed to let the Rebels occupy their home.

[[File:ArbraBaseDoor.jpg|thumb|left|150px|Entrance of Haven Base]]
The main underground cavern and its many offshoots proved vast enough to house nearly eight thousand Rebels, their equipment, vehicles and facilities. A camouflaged, blast-shielded door sealed off the entrance grotto, where engineers built hangar facilities for Rebel ships. Additional tunnels were built to provide alternate escape routes for personnel and [[GR-75 medium transport/Legends|transports]]. Other facilities included briefing rooms, soldiers' and officers' quarters, laboratories, a mess hall and -- in a particularly immense cavern -- the [[Great Hall (Arbra)|Great Hall]], used for larger gatherings and ceremonies. All these areas were organized as numbered modules.

The surrounding wilderness was regularly patrolled by camouflaged [[T-47 airspeeder/Legends|T-47 airspeeders]], while Rebel sentries stood guard outside the grotto entrance. The [[Alliance Fleet/Legends|Rebel fleet]], originally maintaining [[Orbit/Legends|orbit]] around Arbra, was eventually hidden inside the [[Star/Legends|star]] [[Arbran]]'s chromosphere using a number of [[Kerts-Bhrg field generator]]s.

Haven Base was maintained by the Alliance until around the formation of the [[Alliance of Free Planets]].

